        <div class="pt-2">
            <p>Iterative statements are used to run the same block of code over and over again for a certain number of times.</p>
            <p><strong>In PHP, we have the following loops:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>while Loop</li>
                <li>do-while Loop</li>
                <li>for Loop</li>
                <li>foreach loop</li>
            </ol>

            <h1 class="h3">1. While Loop</h1>
            <p>The While loop in PHP is used when we need to execute a block of code again and again based on a given condition. If the condition never becomes false, the while loop keeps getting executed. Such a loop is known as an infinite loop.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
            <pre class="bg-black text-white p-2"><code>&lt;?php
$x = 1;
while ($x &lt;= 10) {
    echo "The number is: $x &lt;br&gt;";
    $x++;
}
?&gt;</code></pre>

            <h1 class="h3">2. Do-While Loop</h1>
            <p>The do-while loop is similar to a while loop except that it is guaranteed to execute at least once. After executing a part of a program for once, the rest of the code gets executed based on a given boolean condition.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
            <pre class="bg-black text-white p-2"><code>&lt;?php
$x = 10;
do {
    echo "The number is: $x &lt;br&gt;";
    $x++;
} while ($x &lt;= 9);
?&gt;</code></pre>

            <h1 class="h3">3. For Loop</h1>
            <p>The for loop is used to iterate a block of code multiple times.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
            <pre class="bg-black text-white p-2"><code>&lt;?php
for ($x = 0; $x &lt;= 10; $x++) {
    echo "The number is: $x &lt;br&gt;";
}
?&gt;</code></pre>

            <h1 class="h3">4. Foreach Loop</h1>
            <p>The foreach loop in PHP can be used to access the array indexes in PHP. It only works on arrays and objects.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
            <pre class="bg-black text-white p-2" ><code>&lt;?php
echo "Welcome to the world of foreach loops &lt;br&gt;";
$arr = array("Bananas", "Apples", "Harpic", "Bread", "Butter");
foreach ($arr as $value) {
    echo "$value &lt;br&gt;";
}
?&gt;</code></pre>
